        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Automation_CheckApplicationTimeFrameAndProcessing",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to determine whether billing processing can commence for a given invoice account group. It checks the current application time frame against the next billing period and evaluates if the billing for the specified utility has already been processed. The procedure returns notes on the application time frame and utility processing status, along with a flag indicating whether processing can start."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple database queries, conditional logic, and utilizes a user-defined function ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "dbo.CalculateNextBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "). While the logic is straightforward, the interaction with multiple tables and the use of a function elevate its complexity to a medium level."
        }
      ]
